  <properties>
    <title>MyBatis Hazelcast | Reference Documentation</title>
    <author email="mybatis-dev@googlegroups.com">The MyBatis Team</author>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="MyBatis EHCache integration - Reference Documentation">

    <p><a href="http://www.hazelcast.com/">Hazelcast</a> is an open source clustering and highly scalable data distribution
  platform for Java.</p>
            <p>Users that want to use Hazelcast into their applications, have to download the <?eval ${project.version}?> zip
            <a href="http://code.google.com/p/mybatis/downloads/list?q=Product-Cache">zip bundle</a>, decompress it and add the jars in the classpath;
            Apache Maven users instead can simply add in
            the <code>pom.xml</code> the following dependency:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[<dependencies>
  ...
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.mybatis.caches</groupId>
    <artifactId>mybatis-hazelcast</artifactId>
    <version>X.X.X</version>
  </dependency>
  ...
</dependencies>]]></source>
            <p>then, just configure it in the mapper XML</p>
            <source><![CDATA[<mapper namespace="org.acme.FooMapper">

  <cache type="org.mybatis.caches.hazelcast.HazelcastCache"/>

  ...

</mapper>]]></source>
            <p>If users need to log cache operations, they can plug the Cache logging version:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[<mapper namespace="org.acme.FooMapper">

  <cache type="org.mybatis.caches.hazelcast.LoggingHazelcastCache"/>

  ...

</mapper>]]></source>
            <p>Please refer to the official Hazelcast Near Cache
            <a href="http://www.hazelcast.com/documentation.jsp#MapNearCache">documentation</a>
            to know more details how to configure Hazelcast as Cache.</p>
        </section>
